The paper discusses the performance of Artificial Intelligence algorithms in social interactions and coordination games, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance of humans against these algorithms, which is related to Game Theory (cs.GT). The use of learning algorithms and the comparison of human and machine performance suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the focus on human-machine interaction and experimental evaluation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
